                                <ns0:remarks>The ZeBanC biobank is one of five biobanks (Berlin, Aachen, Heidelberg, Kiel, W&#252;rzburg) funded by the Bundesministerium f&#252;r Bildung und Forschung (BMBF - Federal Ministry of Education and Research). Apart from establishing a biobank at their particular sites the five biobanks also obliged themselves to develop example processes and best practice methods that can be used by other hospitals building a biobank in the future.
In addition to the activities of those five biobanks the "Technologie- und Methodenplattform f&#252;r vernetzte Forschung e.V. (TMS) develops a nationwide Biobank Registry which is supposed to list all German biobanks.</ns0:remarks>
